<H2>How HTML's FORM Element Works</H2>

The following HTML:
<pre>
&lt;FORM ACTION="<A
HREF="./formval.plaintext">
http://eee.uci.edu/96b/36246/cgi-bin/formval.cgi</A>" METHOD=POST>
&lt;INPUT TYPE=HIDDEN NAME="Secret" VALUE="Quiet">
First entry: &lt;INPUT NAME="Entry1">
&lt;BR>Second Entry: &lt;INPUT NAME="Entry2" VALUE="Anteater">
&lt;BR>Select Color: &lt;SELECT NAME="Color">
   &lt;OPTION VALUE="Rd">Red
   &lt;OPTION VALUE="Gr">Green
   &lt;OPTION VALUE="Bl">Blue
   &lt;/SELECT>
&lt;BR>
&lt;INPUT TYPE=submit NAME=submit Value="Submit Information"> 
&lt;INPUT TYPE=reset NAME=reset Value="Clear Form"> 
&lt;/FORM>
</pre>

<P>Appears as follows:<BR>
<FORM ACTION="http://eee.uci.edu/96b/36246/cgi-bin/formval.cgi"
METHOD=POST>
<INPUT TYPE=HIDDEN NAME="Secret" VALUE="Quiet">
First entry: <INPUT NAME="Entry1"> 
<br>Second Entry: <INPUT NAME="Entry2" VALUE="Anteater"> 
<br>Select Color: <SELECT NAME="Color"> 
<OPTION VALUE="Rd">Red
<OPTION VALUE="Gr">Green
<OPTION VALUE="Bl">Blue
</SELECT>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE=submit NAME=submit Value="Submit Information"> 
<INPUT TYPE=reset NAME=reset Value="Clear Form"> 
</FORM>

<P>
Suggested by
<A HREF="http://www.utoronto.ca/webdocs/HTMLdocs/NewHTML/forms.html">
<tt>http://www.utoronto.ca/webdocs/HTMLdocs/NewHTML/forms.html</tt></A>
<P>
<A HREF="../index.html">ICS 1C, Summer 1996</A>

